et\nflurry. Nothing had such a potent\neffect in breaking the bark of, the\nlui.; --ney as the eon (\"em-;\nplation of the unt M harvests of the\ncountry, with which the nation c.ou Id\ncommand the gold needed to .restore\nconfidence and credit and keep, the\nwheels revolving. Our cotton and\nour corn,' were a ready assetl piled up\nIn our warehnn'ses and granaries,, the\nvalue of'whlch Hdmltted or.no doubt\nor debate. In any quarter, assuring fi\nnancial solvency. I\nKlks In' St.,, Loire, used fh'l'rteen\nlarge delivery wagons to deliver bas\nkets ;on .Christmas at' the homes\"of\nthe poor. More than lSOhomeS.\nmost pi.tbem on the verge of desti\ntution, were made happy by the early\nmorning .calls of. representatives of\nth4,p, P.' 0. E- Ech wagon was\naccorflpaniei by a committee of three\nElks..',, who personally investigated\neach as,e on if docket before taking\nthe ..'basket Inside,' o that pe un\nworthy family miht receive food t\nthe expenee of a worthy one. The\norder is on that can always he de-\npended upon to d\". the right thlvg at\nthe, right lime' and in'tlie right whj.\ny Ttpf Ienns.vlanlH railroad has\n,1u)lt ime,. hundred steel paicnger\naif' lt.( example should ho fol\nlowed by every railroad In the coun\ntry, In the Interest, of tho safety of\nthertravellng public. It uweatary.\nIcgliilatliiu should be cnactrd for\nbidding-thP tine of wooden coaches\nsfer a certain future date, as was\ndone In the cane of safely. appliance.\nThe Chicago Northwestern is\ntiNlng a gasoline motor car on Its\nlines 'west 'of the Missouri river w l' h\nwhat aro underwood lo be very- sat\ntuf..i.ifii'i' i'auiiW- The ,.u, in nresetit\nI.. I,,.. I,.l.n V,,lf,,IUi\n\nS ill liji'iniM'i\nNeb., and P.onesieel. S. I)., iiiHkliig\nthe trip ot 'l5S miles dully In each\ndirection,\nOver 1 in,f)ni,no( is annually\nspent for education In the' United\nStates, without counting tho amount,\nconnected with athletic sports. The\nfact h-lps to explain -the high char-\nacler of American